cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the training and evaluation of word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text classification, information retrieval, and language modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of corpus selection, which is relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
